redlineAn80iIfMib.name: redlineAn80iIfMib
redlineAn80iIfMib.description: This MIB module contains object definitions applicable only to Redline AN80i module.

an80iIfModReduction.name: an80iIfModReduction
an80iIfModReduction.description: Applies when the adaptive rate is disabled, and specifies how many levels the system must drop in modulation before beginning retransmission to address packet errors.

an80iIfAdaptiveMod.name: an80iIfAdaptiveMod
an80iIfAdaptiveMod.description: If enabled, the system automatically adjust the modulation to obtain the maximum throughput.

an80iIfUncodedBurstRate.name: an80iIfUncodedBurstRate
an80iIfUncodedBurstRate.description: The maximum index of the link uncoded burst rate. The rate also depends on the channel width. The possible values are 0..7.

an80iIfEncryptionKey.name: an80iIfEncryptionKey
an80iIfEncryptionKey.description: The Encryption Key used for the AN-80i. Enter the MAC address of the peer equipment to enable over-the-air data encryption.

an80iIfPacketRetransControl.name: an80iIfPacketRetransControl
an80iIfPacketRetransControl.description: Enables/disables packet retransmission. The retransmission scheme is based on the Acknowledge /Request (ARQ) algorithm that detects when packets are lost and makes a request to the MAC scheduler to repeat transmission of the lost packets.

an80iIfLinkLenMode.name: an80iIfLinkLenMode
an80iIfLinkLenMode.description: In manual mode the system uses the user-supplied value for link length. In the auto mode the system calculate itself the distance, which can be read using 'calculated distance'.

an80iIfCurrUncodedBurstRate.name: an80iIfCurrUncodedBurstRate
an80iIfCurrUncodedBurstRate.description: Indicates the index of the link uncoded burst rate. With adaptive modulation enabled, this rate may change over time.

an80iIfPtpLinkStatus.name: an80iIfPtpLinkStatus
an80iIfPtpLinkStatus.description: Indicates if the link has been established/not established.

an80iIfRxPackets.name: an80iIfRxPackets
an80iIfRxPackets.description: Indicates the number of received wireless packets with a correct CRC.

an80iIfRxPacketsReTx.name: an80iIfRxPacketsReTx
an80iIfRxPacketsReTx.description: Indicates the number of received retransmitted wireless packets with a correct CRC.

an80iIfRxPacketsDisc.name: an80iIfRxPacketsDisc
an80iIfRxPacketsDisc.description: Indicates the number of received retransmitted wireless packets with bad CRC.

an80iIfTxPackets.name: an80iIfTxPackets
an80iIfTxPackets.description: Indicates the number of transmitted packets that were received correctly by the other equipment.

an80iIfTxPacketsReTx.name: an80iIfTxPacketsReTx
an80iIfTxPacketsReTx.description: Indicates the number of retransmitted wireless packets received correctly by the other equipment.

an80iIfTxPacketsDisc.name: an80iIfTxPacketsDisc
an80iIfTxPacketsDisc.description: Indicates the number of retransmitted wireless packets that were not received correctly by the other equipment

an80iIfRssiMin.name: an80iIfRssiMin
an80iIfRssiMin.description: Indicates the minimum received signal strength for the measuring interval.

an80iIfRssiMean.name: an80iIfRssiMean
an80iIfRssiMean.description: Indicates the average received signal strength for the measuring interval.

an80iIfRssiMax.name: an80iIfRssiMax
an80iIfRssiMax.description: Indicates the maximum received signal strength for the measuring interval.

an80iIfAvrSinAdr.name: an80iIfAvrSinAdr
an80iIfAvrSinAdr.description: Indicates the Signal to interference, noise and distortion ratio.

an80iIfLastMissedMacAddress.name: an80iIfLastMissedMacAddress
an80iIfLastMissedMacAddress.description: MAC address for the last SS that attempted to register but it was not present in the 'Links' table

an80iIfLastRegistMacAddress.name: an80iIfLastRegistMacAddress
an80iIfLastRegistMacAddress.description: MAC address for the last SS that successfuly registered

an80iIfDenyMacAddress.name: an80iIfDenyMacAddress
an80iIfDenyMacAddress.description: MAC address for the SS that will be denied by this SC

an80iIfLastRegistLinkId.name: an80iIfLastRegistLinkId
an80iIfLastRegistLinkId.description: The link ID for the last SS that successfully registered

an80iIfPmpLinkConfigTable.name: an80iIfPmpLinkConfigTable
an80iIfPmpLinkConfigTable.description: This table contains the PMP link configuration information.

an80iIfPmpLinkConfigEntry.name: an80iIfPmpLinkConfigEntry
an80iIfPmpLinkConfigEntry.description: This table provides one row for each PMP link that has been configured in the SC.

an80iIfPmpLinkPeerMacAddress.name: an80iIfPmpLinkPeerMacAddress
an80iIfPmpLinkPeerMacAddress.description: The MAC address for the peer SS

an80iIfPmpLinkULBurstRate.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULBurstRate
an80iIfPmpLinkULBurstRate.description: User supplied index of the uplink uncoded burst rate.

an80iIfPmpLinkDLBurstRate.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLBurstRate
an80iIfPmpLinkDLBurstRate.description: User supplied index of the downlink uncoded burst rate.

an80iIfPmpLinkConfigStatus.name: an80iIfPmpLinkConfigStatus
an80iIfPmpLinkConfigStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfPmpLinkStatsTable.name: an80iIfPmpLinkStatsTable
an80iIfPmpLinkStatsTable.description: This table contains the PMP link statistics information.

an80iIfPmpLinkStatsEntry.name: an80iIfPmpLinkStatsEntry
an80iIfPmpLinkStatsEntry.description: This table provides one row for each PMP link that has been configured in the Service Controller.

an80iIfPmpLinkStatus.name: an80iIfPmpLinkStatus
an80iIfPmpLinkStatus.description: Indicates if the link has been established/not established.

an80iIfPmpLinkStatusCode.name: an80iIfPmpLinkStatusCode
an80iIfPmpLinkStatusCode.description: Indicates the error code for the link.

an80iIfRegPmpLinkConns.name: an80iIfRegPmpLinkConns
an80iIfRegPmpLinkConns.description: Indicates the registered connections for this Link.

an80iIfPmpLinkUpTime.name: an80iIfPmpLinkUpTime
an80iIfPmpLinkUpTime.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) elapsed since the link was established (up) last time.

an80iIfPmpLinkLostCount.name: an80iIfPmpLinkLostCount
an80iIfPmpLinkLostCount.description: Number of times the link has been lost since the system started.

an80iIfPmpLinkCurrDLUncBurstRate.name: an80iIfPmpLinkCurrDLUncBurstRate
an80iIfPmpLinkCurrDLUncBurstRate.description: Indicates the index of the link's downlink actual uncoded burst rate.

an80iIfPmpLinkDLRssi.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLRssi
an80iIfPmpLinkDLRssi.description: Indicates the link's DL RSSI (Received Signal Strength Indicator).

an80iIfPmpLinkDLSinAdr.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLSinAdr
an80iIfPmpLinkDLSinAdr.description: Indicates the link's DL SINADR (Signal Interference and Noise Distorsion Ratio).

an80iIfPmpLinkDLLostFrm.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLLostFrm
an80iIfPmpLinkDLLostFrm.description: Indicates the link's DL lost frames.

an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksTot.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksTot
an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksTot.description: Indicates the link's DL blocks transmitted.

an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksRetr.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksRetr
an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksRetr.description: Indicates the link's DL block re-transmitted.

an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksDisc.name: an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksDisc
an80iIfPmpLinkDLBlksDisc.description: Indicates the link's DL blocks lost

an80iIfPmpLinkCurrULUncBurstRate.name: an80iIfPmpLinkCurrULUncBurstRate
an80iIfPmpLinkCurrULUncBurstRate.description: Indicates the index of the link's uplink actual uncoded burst rate.

an80iIfPmpLinkULRssi.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULRssi
an80iIfPmpLinkULRssi.description: Indicates the link's UL RSSI (Received Signal Strength Indicator).

an80iIfPmpLinkULSinAdr.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULSinAdr
an80iIfPmpLinkULSinAdr.description: Indicates the link's UL SINADR (Signal Interference and Noise Distorsion Ratio).

an80iIfPmpLinkULLostFrm.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULLostFrm
an80iIfPmpLinkULLostFrm.description: Indicates the link's UL lost frames.

an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksTot.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksTot
an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksTot.description: Indicates the link's UL blocks transmitted.

an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksRetr.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksRetr
an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksRetr.description: Indicates the link's UL block re-transmitted.

an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksDisc.name: an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksDisc
an80iIfPmpLinkULBlksDisc.description: Indicates the link's UL blocks lost

an80iIfPmpLinkStatsStatus.name: an80iIfPmpLinkStatsStatus
an80iIfPmpLinkStatsStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfPmpGroupConfigTable.name: an80iIfPmpGroupConfigTable
an80iIfPmpGroupConfigTable.description: This table contains group configuration information. The group defined as a broadcast domain.

an80iIfPmpGroupConfigEntry.name: an80iIfPmpGroupConfigEntry
an80iIfPmpGroupConfigEntry.description: This table provides one row for each group defined in the Service Controller

an80iIfPmpGroupTaggingControl.name: an80iIfPmpGroupTaggingControl
an80iIfPmpGroupTaggingControl.description: Specifies tagging mode.Only one pass-through group can exist. This is the default group. In the pass-through mode all the Ethernet packets that do not have a VLAN tag or an undefined VID will be classified in this group.

an80iIfPmpGroupVlanId.name: an80iIfPmpGroupVlanId
an80iIfPmpGroupVlanId.description: In the tagged mode all Ethernet packets that have this VID will be classified to belong to this group.

an80iIfPmpGroupDefPriority.name: an80iIfPmpGroupDefPriority
an80iIfPmpGroupDefPriority.description: This field is used every time a tag is added at the exit point. The priority will be the one specified at the entry point.

an80iIfPmpGroupSCEtherControl.name: an80iIfPmpGroupSCEtherControl
an80iIfPmpGroupSCEtherControl.description: Makes the Sector Controller a member of the group.

an80iIfPmpGroupQosLevel.name: an80iIfPmpGroupQosLevel
an80iIfPmpGroupQosLevel.description: QoS level (index) that will affect the bandwidth and the delay for this group.

an80iIfPmpGroupConfigStatus.name: an80iIfPmpGroupConfigStatus
an80iIfPmpGroupConfigStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfPmpGroupRate.name: an80iIfPmpGroupRate
an80iIfPmpGroupRate.description: Define the index of the group rate. (0..7, 8=auto)

an80iIfPmpGroupSStoSSMulticast.name: an80iIfPmpGroupSStoSSMulticast
an80iIfPmpGroupSStoSSMulticast.description: Enable the Subscriber to subscriber multicast traffic.

an80iIfPmpGroupStatsTable.name: an80iIfPmpGroupStatsTable
an80iIfPmpGroupStatsTable.description: This table contains group statistics information. The group defined as a broadcast domain.

an80iIfPmpGroupStatsEntry.name: an80iIfPmpGroupStatsEntry
an80iIfPmpGroupStatsEntry.description: This table provides one row for each group defined in the Service Controller

an80iIfPmpGroupPacketsTx.name: an80iIfPmpGroupPacketsTx
an80iIfPmpGroupPacketsTx.description: Broadcast/multicast Ethernet packets classified and transmitted to the group.

an80iIfPmpGroupPacketDisc.name: an80iIfPmpGroupPacketDisc
an80iIfPmpGroupPacketDisc.description: Ethernet packets classified to be sent to the group but discarded due to unavailable memory.

an80iIfPmpGroupStatsStatus.name: an80iIfPmpGroupStatsStatus
an80iIfPmpGroupStatsStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfPmpConnConfigTable.name: an80iIfPmpConnConfigTable
an80iIfPmpConnConfigTable.description: This table contains connections configuration information. One connection defines the transport parameter for Ethernet packets that have specific properties.

an80iIfPmpConnConfigEntry.name: an80iIfPmpConnConfigEntry
an80iIfPmpConnConfigEntry.description: This table provides one row for each connection defined in the Service Controller

an80iIfPmpConnTaggingControl.name: an80iIfPmpConnTaggingControl
an80iIfPmpConnTaggingControl.description: Specifies tagging mode. Only one pass-through connection can be defined on each link. This is the default connection. All the untagged packets or with a VID that is not defined will be transmitted on this connection.

an80iIfPmpConnVlanId.name: an80iIfPmpConnVlanId
an80iIfPmpConnVlanId.description: Specifies VLAN Id for the tagged mode.

an80iIfPmpConnDefPriority.name: an80iIfPmpConnDefPriority
an80iIfPmpConnDefPriority.description: This field is used every time a tag is added at the exit point. The priority will be the one specified at the entry point.

an80iIfPmpConnDefParentLink.name: an80iIfPmpConnDefParentLink
an80iIfPmpConnDefParentLink.description: This object specifies the parent link of the connection.

an80iIfPmpConnDefParenGroup.name: an80iIfPmpConnDefParenGroup
an80iIfPmpConnDefParenGroup.description: This object specifies the parent group of the connection.

an80iIfPmpConnDLQos.name: an80iIfPmpConnDLQos
an80iIfPmpConnDLQos.description: Connection QoS level (index) that will affect the DL bandwidth and the delay.

an80iIfPmpConnULQos.name: an80iIfPmpConnULQos
an80iIfPmpConnULQos.description: Connection QoS level (index) that will affect the UL bandwidth and the delay.

an80iIfPmpConnConfigStatus.name: an80iIfPmpConnConfigStatus
an80iIfPmpConnConfigStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfPmpConnStatsTable.name: an80iIfPmpConnStatsTable
an80iIfPmpConnStatsTable.description: This table contains connections configuration information. One connection defines the transport parameter for Ethernet packets that have specific properties.

an80iIfPmpConnStatsEntry.name: an80iIfPmpConnStatsEntry
an80iIfPmpConnStatsEntry.description: This table provides one row for each connection defined in the Service Controller

an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsTx.name: an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsTx
an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsTx.description: Indicates Ethernet packets sent by SC.

an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsDisc.name: an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsDisc
an80iIfPmpConnDLPacketsDisc.description: Indicates packets discarded due to full buffer.

an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsTx.name: an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsTx
an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsTx.description: Indicates Ethernet packets sent by SS.

an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsDisc.name: an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsDisc
an80iIfPmpConnULPacketsDisc.description: Indicates packets discarded due to full buffer.

an80iIfPmpConnStatsStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or modify or delete an existing row in this table.

an80iIfRegistrationFailedTrap.name: an80iIfRegistrationFailedTrap
an80iIfRegistrationFailedTrap.description: Event that reports the failure of a registration attempt of a SS that is not defined in the link table.

an80iIfRegistrationOKTrap.name: an80iIfRegistrationOKTrap
an80iIfRegistrationOKTrap.description: An event to report the successful SS registration.

redlineAn80iIfNotificationGroup.name: redlineAn80iIfNotificationGroup
redlineAn80iIfNotificationGroup.description: The notifications which indicate specific events within the AN80i interface.

redlineAn80iIfCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities that implement this MIB module.
